A Fischer esterification of the same ketoacid (III) is carried out with an alcohol ROH to afford the corresponding ester (VII). This ester is brominated under similar conditions as the amide (IV) described above, to yield bromoketoesters (VIII). A cyclization with aminopyridazines (VI) allows the preparation of the imidazopyridazines (II) substituted with an ester group. Finally, acylic substitution by using a substituted hydrazine in a suitable solvent at reflux provides the corresponding hydrazides (I, X = CO, R
